studyArms.name: Axicabtagene Ciloleucel
studyArms.description: Subjects receive a 3-day conditioning chemotherapy regimen (fludarabine 30 mg/m2/day and cyclophosphamide 500 mg/m2/day) followed by a single infusion of axicabtagene ciloleucel at a target dose of 2 x 10^6 anti-CD19 CAR T cells/kg.

studyArms.name: Standard of Care (SOC)
studyArms.description: Subjects receive investigator's choice of platinum-based salvage combination chemotherapy (R-ICE, R-DHAP, R-ESHAP, or R-GDP). Responding subjects proceed to high-dose therapy (HDT) and autologous stem cell transplant (ASCT).

arms.name: Axicabtagene Ciloleucel
arms.description: Subjects receive a 3-day conditioning chemotherapy regimen (fludarabine 30 mg/m2/day and cyclophosphamide 500 mg/m2/day) followed by a single infusion of axicabtagene ciloleucel at a target dose of 2 x 10^6 anti-CD19 CAR T cells/kg.

arms.name: Standard of Care (SOC)
arms.description: Subjects receive investigator's choice of platinum-based salvage combination chemotherapy (R-ICE, R-DHAP, R-ESHAP, or R-GDP). Responding subjects proceed to high-dose therapy (HDT) and autologous stem cell transplant (ASCT).

epochs.name: Leukapheresis
epochs.description: Collection of peripheral blood mononuclear cells (Axi-cel arm) or stem cell collection (SOC arm).

epochs.name: Conditioning Chemotherapy
epochs.description: Lymphodepleting regimen for Axi-cel arm or salvage chemotherapy for SOC arm.

epochs.name: IP Administration
epochs.description: Infusion of axicabtagene ciloleucel or ASCT (for SOC responders).

epochs.name: Long-term Follow-up
epochs.description: Monitoring for up to 15 years for Axi-cel subjects.
